    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col p-md-2 m-md-3">
          <h1 class="h3 mt-3">Cookie Policy</h1>
          <p class="text-quaternary"><small>Last updated: July 13, 2026</small></p>

          <p class="mt-3">
            This instance at <strong>nets.n1cck.radio</strong> uses exactly one cookie:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Session cookie (essential)</strong> — a signed, HTTP-only cookie that keeps
              you logged in between requests. It contains no tracking identifiers and is required
              for the service to function; it is removed when you sign out.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <p>
            There are no advertising cookies and no third-party tracking cookies. Analytics on
            this instance is provided by a self-hosted, <strong>cookieless</strong> Plausible
            Analytics server — it sets no cookies and stores no identifiers in your browser.
            Signing in with Google happens on Google's own pages; Google's cookies on
            google.com are governed by Google's policies, and no Google cookie is set on this
            domain.
          </p>

          <p>
            You can clear or block cookies in your browser settings; blocking the session cookie
            will prevent signing in. Questions:
            <a href="mailto:nick@n1cck.us">nick@n1cck.us</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%- include('./partials/pageBottomFeatures') %>
